                   leaders in their respective domains to address these
                   topics. This led to a wide consultation process,
                   involving an international group of experts in key
                   aspects of DBCI development, evaluation, and usage,
                   drawn from the disciplines of behavioral and social
                   science, medicine, public health, health services
                   research, computer science and engineer-ing, and
                   economics. Participants were invited to join writing
                   groups relating to each topic and to attend a 2-day
                   workshop held in London in September 2015. The
                   writing groups produced an initial draft of each
                   paper for presentation for in-depth discussion at the
