                   and Extraversion. The findings suggest that measures
                   of depression and positive emotions/cheerfulness are
                   necessary and sufficient to predict life satisfaction
                   from personality traits. The results also lead to a
                   more refined understanding of the specific
                   personality traits that influence life satisfaction:
                   Depression is more important than anxiety or anger
